HEADWORD: Lamaism
<hw>La"ma*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A modified form of
Buddhism which prevails in Tibet, Mongolia, and some adjacent parts of
Asia; -- so called from the name of its priests. See 2d
<er>Lama</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

